cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new optimization method for reinforcement learning. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as reinforcement learning is often used in robotics applications. It may also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as reinforcement learning is used in control systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as reinforcement learning is used in computer vision applications such as object recognition and tracking.
